25|$|In 1772, {{an episode}} in Marseille {{involved}} the non-lethal incapacitating of prostitutes with the supposed aphrodisiac Spanish fly and <b>sodomy</b> with Latour, his manservant. That year, {{the two men}} were sentenced to death in absentia for <b>sodomy</b> and the poisoning. They fled to Italy, Sade taking his wife's sister with him. Sade and Latour were caught and imprisoned at the Fortress of Miolans in late 1772, but escaped four months later.|$|E
